    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-047" from="REQ-CMD-010" to="REQ-CMD-009" type="dependsOn">
      <notes>Coding agent command generation (REQ-CMD-010) depends on implementation planning (REQ-CMD-009) as /cmd generates instructions from the latest /plan output.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-048" from="REQ-CMD-009" to="GOAL-SE-PRINCIPLES" type="satisfies">
      <notes>Implementation planning (REQ-CMD-009) satisfies the goal of preserving software engineering rigor by enforcing spec-first planning before code generation.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-049" from="REQ-CMD-010" to="GOAL-LLM-CONTEXT" type="satisfies">
      <notes>Coding agent command generation (REQ-CMD-010) satisfies the goal of maintaining LLM coding context by providing structured, spec-derived prompts to coding agents.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-050" from="REQ-CMD-007" to="GOAL-SE-PRINCIPLES" type="satisfies">
      <notes>Spec quality commands (REQ-CMD-007) satisfy the goal of preserving software engineering rigor by providing quality assessment and linting of the specification.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-051" from="REQ-CMD-012" to="REQ-CMD-001" type="dependsOn">
      <notes>Command Palette access (REQ-CMD-012) depends on the slash command interface (REQ-CMD-001) as palette commands delegate to the same handlers.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
    <traceEdge id="TR-052" from="REQ-CMD-012" to="REQ-AGT-001" type="dependsOn">
      <notes>Command Palette access (REQ-CMD-012) depends on the agent panel tab (REQ-AGT-001) as the output destination for palette-invoked commands.</notes>
    </traceEdge>
  </trace>
</rqml>